00:13:57.903 --> 00:14:00.205 align:start size:94% position:6%
<i> with them getting less sleep
 than is recommended</i>

00:14:00.305 --> 00:14:02.374 align:start size:78% position:22%
<i> for their
 developing brains.</i>

00:14:02.474 --> 00:14:05.143 align:start size:91% position:9%
<i> Among the third of children
 who had optimal bedtimes</i>

00:14:05.243 --> 00:14:07.813
<i> and sleep routines
 between 5 and 9,</i>

00:14:07.913 --> 00:14:11.516
<i> well, their body mass index
 was lower at 15 years old.</i>

00:14:11.616 --> 00:14:14.419 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> And their good
 sleep habits continued.</i>

00:14:14.519 --> 00:14:16.222 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> A study from
 Penn State last year</i>

00:14:16.322 --> 00:14:19.091
<i> showed that giving kids
 screen time before bed</i>

00:14:19.191 --> 00:14:21.660 align:start position:0%
<i>led to about an hour less sleep
and a higher BMI.</i>

00:14:22.961 --> 00:14:25.464 align:start size:84% position:16%
The study shows
it's time to slow down

00:14:25.564 --> 00:14:27.333
